title: Kidderminster Harriers FA Cup tickets sell out in 20 minutes
text:
Tweet 
An extra 105 tickets for the fourth qualifying round tie went on sale at 9am this morning from the Aggborough ticket office and eager fans wasted no time in snapping them up - with the club announcing at 9.20am all tickets had been sold. A d GONE! All 100 tickets sold in less than 20 minutes. Well done you lot! — Official Harriers (@khfcofficial) October 21, 2015 
The game is one of the biggest non-league games in the Midlands for years and is presently the talk of both towns, with a crowd of more than 2,000 expected to pack into Stour’s War Memorial Ground. What do you think?
